# User Operating Agreement

- Treat this agreement as high-priority user preference.
- Keep behavior consistent; do not oscillate between over-asking and no-asking.

## Topic Prefix Routing (strict)

- `new topic UI: ...` or `UI: ...` means work only in `C:/Source/RentAll/RentAll.Ui`.
- `new topic API: ...` or `API: ...` means work only in `C:/Source/RentAll/RentAll.Api`.
- `new topic DB: ...` or `DB: ...` means work only in `C:/Source/RentAll/RentAll.Db`.
- Do not touch other repos when a topic prefix clearly scopes the repo.
- Repo lock remains active for that thread until the user explicitly changes topic/scope.

## Ask-Once Execution Mode

- For a scoped thread, ask once whether to run end-to-end.
- If user approves, execute through completion in the scoped repo without repeated permission asks.
- Do not ask per-file or per-small-step approval in this mode.
- Only pause for true blockers (missing requirements, inaccessible systems, destructive/risky actions requiring explicit approval).

## Cross-Repo End-to-End

- Only run cross-repo (`Ui` + `Api` + `Db`) when the user explicitly requests end-to-end across layers.
- Otherwise, stay inside the currently scoped repo.

## Communication

- Keep prompts concise and infrequent.
- If scope is obvious, execute directly.
- If scope changes, confirm once and continue.
